longBusinessSummary: GNB Financial Services, Inc. operates as a bank holding company for The Gratz Bank, a full-service state chartered commercial bank in Pennsylvania. Its deposit products include interest- and noninterest-bearing checking accounts, saving accounts, certificates of deposit, and individual retirement accounts. The company's loan portfolio comprises consumer loans, such as home mortgage, home equity, construction, vehicle, and other personal loans, as well as lines of credit; and business loans, including agricultural, term, construction, and vehicle loans, as well as commercial mortgages, lines of credit, and letters of credit. It also provides debit and merchant card, bill payment, safe deposit box, notary, reorder check, and other services, as well as online, mobile, and telephone banking services. The company operates through a main office located in Gratz, Pennsylvania, as well as branch offices located in Valley View, Herndon, Pottsville, Trevorton, and Minersville, Pennsylvania. GNB Financial Services, Inc. was founded in 1934 and is based in Gratz, Pennsylvania.
